{"key":"post-14471916","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>14471916</id>\n<content>Turn your stove as high as it goes until just before full pressure is reached.&amp;nbsp; There is no reason to waste time heating water slowly.&amp;nbsp; Also, the rocker shouldn't be allowed to rattle.&amp;nbsp; We're not canning fruit, we're 'misusing' a pressure cooker as a sterilizer.&amp;nbsp; Bring to pressure, reduce heat until the rocker either stops rocking or only rattles once a minute or so at most.&amp;nbsp; Don't use a cheap chinese PC without a pressure gauge.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You're supposed to use fine verm for brf cakes, not course.&amp;nbsp; If there's settling, it sounds like you didn't tap the sides of the jars after filling to get the air pockets out.&amp;nbsp; I also sometimes pile the verm 1/8&quot; or so above the jar before putting the lid on.&amp;nbsp; This allows a bit of extra to account for any settling that may occur.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>14471941</next>\n<prev>14471863</prev>\n<first>14471750</first>\n<last>14471941</last>\n<when>1305722119</when>\n<utime>05/18/11 03:35 PM</utime>\n</post>"}